.TH PRINTLN 3 "July 2026" "libctools" "C Library Functions"
.SH NAME
println \- formatted output conversion with trailing newline (thread-safe on hosted systems)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <libctools.h>
.HP
.BI "void println(const char *" format ", ...);"
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR println ()
function writes output under the control of a
.I format
string that specifies how subsequent arguments are converted for output. A newline character ('\\n') is automatically appended to the end of the output.
.SH AVAILABILITY
The behavior of
.BR println ()
adapts dynamically depending on the compilation target:
.TP
.B Desktop / Hosted (stdc)
Outputs directly to 
.IR stdout .
The function internally invokes
.BR flockfile (3)
prior to writing, and
.BR funlockfile (3)
upon completion. This guarantees that the output block and its trailing newline are written atomically, preventing thread interleaving.
.TP
.B Embedded / Bare-metal (embedc)
Outputs via the platform's registered hardware serial port (UART). Thread locking primitives are omitted unless explicitly supported by the target RTOS architecture.
.SH RETURN VALUE
None.
